Consider the following:

``` mlir
module {
  om.class @Foo(%input: !om.integer)  -> () {
    om.class.fields
  }
  om.class @Bar(%basepath: !om.frozenbasepath) {
    %0 = om.constant #om.integer<42 : si64> : !om.integer
    %1 = om.object @Foo(%0) : (!om.integer) -> !om.class.type<@Foo>
    %2 = om.object.field %1, [@usedField] : (!om.class.type<@Foo>) -> !om.integer
    om.class.fields
  }
}
```

There is not field "usedField", however, this doesn't trip any verifier error.

This is possibly related to https://github.com/llvm/circt/issues/7078.
